Olympic Air Cuts Flights to European Capitals in Route Reshuffle

-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 
2011-03-03T08:14:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/olympic-air-cuts-flights-to-european-capitals-in-route-reshuffle.html
Olympic Air, the Greek carrier owned
by  Marfin Investment Group SA (MIG) , said it will discontinue flights
to London, Paris, Brussels and Vienna and add a route to
Belgrade, according to a statement on Olympicâ€™s  website .  The Athens-based airline also said it will add domestic
flights from  Athens  to Corfu and the northern city of
Alexandroupolis and from Thessaloniki to Heraklion, Chania,
Mytilene and Rhodes.  The changes take effect March 27. Flights to Paris will
continue until May 2, the airline said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
